<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFF2FFA8FCB475C8DD71FE8C" blockId="67.[831,1289,239,271]" box="[831,1289,239,271]" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">
<heading id="A5317A4CFFF2FFA8FCB475C8DD71FE8C" box="[831,1289,239,271]" centered="true" fontSize="12" level="2" pageId="67" pageNumber="80" reason="2">
3.8. Genus 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF2FFA8FC4075C8DD71FE8C" authority="FAUVEL, 1905" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1905" box="[971,1289,239,271]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Amaurodera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF2FFA8FC4075C8DC19FE8C" box="[971,1121,239,271]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">Amaurodera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFF2FFA8FBE375C8DD71FE8C" author="FAUVEL, A." box="[1128,1289,239,271]" pageId="67" pageNumber="80" pagination="75 - 86" refId="ref77309" refString="FAUVEL, A. 1905: Staphylinides de Java, recueillis par M. le Dr. K. Kraepelin et M. le Dr. Koningsberger en 1904. - Mitteilungen aus dem Naturhistorischen Museum, Hamburg 22: 75 - 86." type="journal article" year="1905">FAUVEL, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B6DC9EABFFF2FFA8FCB47416DC56FCA2" pageId="67" pageNumber="80" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFF2FFA8FCB47416DC38FECC" blockId="67.[831,1088,305,335]" box="[831,1088,305,335]" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">
<heading id="A5317A4CFFF2FFA8FCB47416DC38FECC" box="[831,1088,305,335]" centered="true" fontSize="12" level="1" pageId="67" pageNumber="80" reason="5">3.8.1. General remarks</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFF2FFA8FC91744EDD6DFD42" blockId="67.[794,1399,361,801]" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">
Including the new species described below and the newly established synonymies, 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF2FFA8FBF474AEDD7EFE22" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1905" box="[1151,1286,393,417]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Amaurodera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF2FFA8FBF474AEDD7EFE22" box="[1151,1286,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">Amaurodera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently includes 46 species (see section 3.8.2). The distribution of the genus is essentially Oriental, with some species (groups) occurring also in the south of the East Palaearctic region; it ranges from the Himalaya to the 
<collectingCountry id="86D18DB0FFF2FFA8FC91770EDBE0FDC2" box="[794,920,553,577]" name="Philippines" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">Philippines</collectingCountry>
. Some species, particularly most of those recorded from the Himalaya, have very restricted distributions, whereas others are remarkably widespread. The latter particularly applies to 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF2FFA8FB1377AEDD58FD22" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1905" box="[1176,1312,649,673]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Amaurodera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraepelini">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF2FFA8FB1377AEDD58FD22" box="[1176,1312,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">A. kraepelini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose distribution ranges from the Himalaya to Java.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFF2FFA8FC9177EEDC56FCA2" blockId="67.[794,1399,361,801]" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">
Since most of the new species are described from 
<collectingCountry id="86D18DB0FFF2FFA8FAB077EEDB34FC82" name="Thailand" pageId="67" pageNumber="80">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, a key to the species recorded from this country is provided in section 3.8.3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
